  p.
    In each color series there are 7 colors: the base color (middle row above) plus 3 incrementally lighter and 3 incrementally darker.

  h3 Applying colors to elements

  p.
    In addition to the colors (optionally) used in the typography and components, Codebase also has a set of #[b decoration classes] for setting colors of text, backgrounds and borders.

  .grid.grid--gutter.b--1px-solid.pt--3u
    .col.col-sm--span-6
      b Backgrounds #[code bg-][color]
    .col.col-sm--span-6
      .p--2u.bg--blue-lighten-3  Example .bg--blue-lighten-3
      br
    .col.col-sm--span-6
      b Borders #[code b-][color]
    .col.col-sm--span-6
      .mb--3u.p--2u.b--4px-solid.b--orange  Example .b--orange
    .col.col-sm--span-6
      b Text #[code text-][color]
    .col.col-sm--span-6
      p.text--teal-darken-1  Example .text--teal-darken-1

